content:
Enable CRM Analytics
 
Before creating an app from the Analytics for Subscriber Lifecycle Management template, enable CRM Analytics in Salesforce.

If you see the Launch CRM Analytics button, it's already enabled. Proceed to assign permissions to admins and users.

From Setup, enter Getting Started, and select Getting Started under Analytics.
Click Enable CRM Analytics.

Assign Permissions
 
 Assign Permissions to Admins and Users
 
In the Quick Find box, search for "Getting Started" and click on it.
Under "Analytics", click on "Enable CRM Analytics".
 

Assign Permissions to Admins and Users

Assign permissions to admins and users by following these steps:
 
In the Quick Find box, enter "User Management" and select User Management.
Click on "Users" and then find the user you want to assign permissions to.
Click on the dropdown menu next to the user's name and select "Edit".
Scroll down to the "Analytics" section and check the boxes for the necessary permissions.
Click "Save".

Assign Permissions to Analytics Integration User

To assign permissions to the analytics integration user, follow these steps:
 
In the Quick Find box, enter "User Management" and select User Management.
Click on "Users" and then find the user you want to assign permissions to.
Click on the dropdown menu next to the user's name and select "Edit".
Scroll down to the "Analytics" section and check the boxes for the necessary permissions.
Check the box next to "Allow this user to create and delete auto-installed apps".
Check the box next to "Allow this user to manage templated apps".
Click "Save".

Set Field-Level Security for Analytics Integration User

To set field-level security for the analytics integration user, follow these steps:
 
In the Quick Find box, enter "User Management" and select User Management.
Click on "Users" and then find the user you want to assign permissions to.
Click on the dropdown menu next to the user's name and select "Edit".
Scroll down to the "Analytics" section and check the boxes for the necessary field-level security settings.
Click "Save".
title: Enabling Salesforce CRM Analytics
